	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Elorg was still experimenting with the rules of <em>Tetris</em> back then. The preview was one of the things that wasn't standardized. In fact, some early games let the player turn preview on and off and gave more points for playing without it. It's certainly not like <a href="http://harddrop.com/wiki/Preview" class="postlink">today</a> where it's effectively a <a href="http://harddrop.com/wiki/Tetris_Guideline" class="postlink">requirement</a> to show at least the next three pieces.<br /><br />Did you try pressing the Select button?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


