	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>lidnariq</b> [ Tue Jun 09, 2015 11:58 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: puNES Emulator (ex Fnes)</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />SDL and DirectX (&quot;<strong>d</strong>irect<strong>3d</strong> version <strong>9</strong>&quot;) are both sets of routines that make it easier for the programmer to do graphical things.<br /><br />puNES supports both because one or the other may work better or worse on any given graphics card, or any given version of windows.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


